{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan Ibn Majah","section":{"31":"Chapters on Medicine"},"section_detail":{"31":{"hadithnumber_first":3436,"hadithnumber_last":3549,"arabicnumber_first":3436,"arabicnumber_last":3549}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":3534,"arabicnumber":3534,"text":"Rapporté par ‘Aishah : Le Prophète (ﷺ) a ordonné de tuer Dhit-Tufytain* car elle fait perdre la vue et provoque des fausses couches. (*Cela désigne un serpent dangereux)","grades":[{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Shuaib Al Arnaut","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Sahih Muslim"}],"reference":{"book":31,"hadith":99}}]}